data.title: Slipknot kick off ‘Here Comes The Pain’ Tour
data.meta_description: Slipknot kicked off their Here Comes The Pain tour, celebrating the 25th anniversary of their 1999 self-titled debut album.
data.meta_site_name: Metal Insider | Get Inside the Industry
data.text:
Slipknot kicked off their Here Comes The Pain tour, celebrating the 25th anniversary of their self-titled debut album. The tour began with a sold-out show at the Ruoff Music Center in Noblesville, IN with special guests Knocked Loose, Orbit Culture, and Vended.

The band performed nearly the entire self-titled album, excluding “Diluted.” As promised by vocalist Corey Taylor who once stated, “Nothing you will hear tonight was written after 1999.” The set included tracks “No Life” and “Scissors,” which were performed for the first time since 2000, “Only One” since 2012, and “Me Inside” since 2015.
